def load_dicom_images_path(path , filename, fileextension):

  print (' loading file name from  : ', path + '/' + filename)
  image_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['path', 'patientId'])

  bucket = path
  data_key = filename
  data_location = 's3://{}/{}'.format(bucket, data_key) 
  temp_df = pd.read_csv(data_location)
  
  i = 0  
  for ind in temp_df.index:
      dicom_folder_path = temp_df['path'][ind]
      dicom_image_filename = temp_df['filename'][ind]
      p_id = dicom_image_filename.split('.')[0]
      filepath = dicom_folder_path + dicom_image_filename
      image_df = image_df.append({'path': filepath, 'patientId': p_id}, ignore_index=True)
  
  return image_df

def load_dicom_images_tags(images_path_df, load_image_array):

  image_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['path', 'patientId', 'patientSex', 'patientAge', 'bodyPartExamined', 'viewPosition' ])
  session = boto3.Session()
  s3_session = session.client('s3')

  s3 = boto3.resource('s3')
  bucket = s3.Bucket(root_path)
  objs = list(bucket.objects.filter(Prefix= pickle_output_folder + 'dicom_images_df.pickle'))


   
  if(len(objs)>0):
    print("dicom_images_df.pickle File exists")
    object = s3_session.get_object(Bucket= root_path,Key=pickle_output_folder + 'dicom_images_df.pickle')
    serializedObject = object['Body'].read()
    #Deserialize the retrieved object
    image_df = pickle.loads(serializedObject)
  else:
    print("dicom_images_df.pickle File does not exist")
    for ind in images_path_df.index:
      in_path = images_path_df['path'][ind]
      patientId = images_path_df['patientId'][ind]
      
      fileobj = s3_session.get_object(Bucket=root_path,  Key=in_path )

      # open the file object and read it into the variable dicom_data. 
      dicom_data = fileobj['Body'].read()

      # Read DICOM
      dicom_bytes = DicomBytesIO(dicom_data)
      c_dicom = dcmread(dicom_bytes)  
      #print(c_dicom)
      patientSex = c_dicom.PatientSex #   tmp_np[0]
      patientAge = c_dicom.PatientAge  #tmp_np[1]
      bodyPartExamined = c_dicom.BodyPartExamined #tmp_np[2]
      viewPosition = c_dicom.ViewPosition #tmp_np[3]

      image_df = image_df.append({'path':in_path, 'patientId':patientId, 'patientSex':patientSex ,'patientAge':patientAge, 'bodyPartExamined':bodyPartExamined, 'viewPosition':viewPosition }, ignore_index=True)
      if ind%1000 == 0:
        print(ind)
        print('image_df size ' , sys.getsizeof(image_df))
        

    print('writing pickle file ')
    #Serialize the object 
    serializedDFObject = pickle.dumps(image_df)
    s3_session.put_object(Bucket= root_path,Key= pickle_output_folder + 'dicom_images_df.pickle',Body=serializedDFObject)
      
  return image_df

def missing_data(data):
    total = data.isnull().sum().sort_values(ascending = False)
    percent = (data.isnull().sum()/data.isnull().count()*100).sort_values(ascending = False)
    df = pd.concat([total, percent], axis=1, keys=['Total', 'Percent'])
    df = df.astype(int)
    return np.transpose(df)

for c_ax, (c_path, c_rows) in zip(m_axs.flatten(), sample_df.groupby(['path'])):
  
  #image_bytes = tf.io.read_file(c_path)
  #image = tfio.image.decode_dicom_image(image_bytes, dtype=tf.uint16)
  
  fileobj = s3_session.get_object(Bucket=root_path,  Key=c_path )
  # open the file object and read it into the variable dicom_data. 
  dicom_data = fileobj['Body'].read()

  # Read DICOM
  dicom_bytes = DicomBytesIO(dicom_data)
  c_dicom = dcmread(dicom_bytes)

  c_ax.imshow(np.squeeze(c_dicom.pixel_array), cmap='bone')

  t1 = '{class}'.format(**c_rows.iloc[0,:])
  t2 = '{patientId}'.format(**c_rows.iloc[0,:])
  c_ax.set_title (t1 + '\n' +t2)

  for i, (_, c_row) in enumerate(c_rows.dropna().iterrows()):
      c_ax.plot(c_row['x'], c_row['y'], 's', label='{class}'.format(**c_row))
